replyContent: Hi Charlene. Sorry that there is an issue with the app. We have not had any other reports of the app freezing. We would like to resolve the problem, but need more information. Please contact us at support@snaptwostudio.com.

My faivorte game that makes me feel very very happy

My sons love the game, but as I tried installing it on my youngest son's tablet it prompted me to pay for the app again. There's no way around it even though I'm using the same Google account for all my devices, so I guess it's only going to be on one device.

This was a wonderful game to play, however lately it has glitched up. Whenever I start up either one or two, a screen appears telling me we need to download some more tab here to download. After that the game crashes and I get a notification that bugs and buttons is looking for resources to download. Please help. My three-year-old is pretty disappointed that I can't fix it . I have uninstalled and reinstalled and even done a factory reset on the tablet.

Looking for an app for a toddler with developmental delays to help work on fine motor skills and problem solving and focus and I finally found this. I love it. Can't speak highly enough of it. Have tried every game and they are all beautiful and fun and easy to learn to do. Nothing here is obnoxious or annoying like so many other apps. This one will be useful for a few years I believe. Some really easy parts and some a little more complex. Thanks so much!

The bugs are difficult to control, even for an adult. The butterfly  was impossible to get over the hurdles. What a waste of money, and no refunds after a few hour's  of being installed. Tired of kid's games  bogus positive review's. If google play don't  get their act together and start protecting it's  user's  from false reviewer's  i will retreat to the apple store.
Beautifully rendered, nothing obnoxious, educational and fun.
Brilliant and engaging for my 2 year old

We have this and Bugs and Buttons 2 for android. My kids who are 4, 6, and 8 all love it. They play them regularly. Lots of fun learning activities in each game. I also have Bug Art and Bug Mazing on ipad along with some others that are ipad only at the moment. They had a big package deal of them there. Highly recommend.
My preschooler's teacher showed me this, she uses it with her student. My daughter loves it I had to get it myself

Although it doesn't take much to get a 2 year olds attention with a bright screen...she does love this game. Some of the games are for older kids but that's ok. That means this game will last more than a few months! Good game. No glitches or force closes.  ★★★★★
Very good game for kids
Excellent for my 4 and 6 year old!
Game is well-designed and age-appropriate. The difficulty adjusts to your child's capability.

Really clever and nicely done. Me and my 3 year old love all the games:) It changes its difficulty depending on the skills of the player. I'll definitely buy the second one too. The only thing I don't like are the cockroaches:) But I still play even those games because they're cool:) This is a perfect app for children. Funny and educational.
It's hard to find truly great apps for young kids. I've spent far more on inferior apps. Lots of fun and educational content! Thank you.
This is a VERY entertaining app. Very realistic and awesome graphics! My kids LOVE this! A big thumbs up!!!
Great therapeutic tool to help kiddos with Dev. Delays would be great for all little ones to master some important skills.

Great games for the little ones. My kid loves most of them. Teaches kids colors, letters, hand/eye coordination, problem solving and other skills. Great job. Keep me posted on upcoming android apps.
